  <TITLE>Static deployment with --local-config=... and a manual directory causes the configuration to be uploaded</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>```console $ cat &gt; now.json &lt;&lt;EOF { &quot;name&quot;: &quot;my-project&quot;, &quot;type&quot;: &quot;static&quot;, &quot;files&quot;: [ &quot;out&quot; ] } EOF $ mkdir out $ echo 'hello' &gt; out/index.html $ now -A `pwd`/now.json out ``` This deploys only the `now.json` and serves it as the index file. The long argument for local config (instead of `-A`) works the same way.</DESCRIPTION>
